pr_body:
this replaces the define OPTFLOW with OPTICAL_FLOW

OPTFLOW is also used in some enums, and as a result it was e.g. not possible to define the usage of optical flow in the hwdef file; writing e.g. "define OPTFLOW 0" did produce errors. This renaming resolves this. It might be a good thing anyway to not have such name overlapping.
